parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS System Malfunction on Uneven Road Surfaces
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) on uneven road surfaces can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or jerks violently when braking on uneven road surfaces
the brakes lock or fail to engage fully
the vehicle continues to roll or lurch forward despite applying the brakes
the ABS system kicks in and launches the vehicle forward
the vehicle stops abruptly or erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked windshield can obstruct the driver's view, causing a safety hazard, and may lead to further damage if not addressed promptly.
symptoms: Cracked windshield
often with no apparent cause or warning signs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A shattered moonroof can cause glass fragments to fall into the vehicle, potentially injuring occupants, and may lead to water damage or other issues if not addressed promptly.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected shattering of the moonroof
often without warning signs or apparent cause.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning ABS system can cause the vehicle to shake or vibrate excessively, making it harder to control and increasing the risk of accidents, especially when stopping or braking.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates dramatically when driving over small potholes or bumps
the ABS system engages without warning
and the brakes may feel spongy or unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rollaway Incident due to Faulty Transmission or Parking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission or parking system can cause the vehicle to roll away unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls away while in park
sudden and unintended movement of the vehicle
inability to control the vehicle's movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping and Loss of Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and loss of acceleration can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: Transmission slips out of gear
engine RPM revs high
vehicle stops accelerating
vehicle feels like it's in neutral
transmission slams into gear
jolting occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The extended gear shifting and jerking can cause the vehicle to accelerate slowly, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: Extended gear shifting
vehicle jerks when shifting into gear
engine revving while accelerating slowly
slow and delayed acceleration.
